name: Eggs
properties: Eggs also contain B12, vitamins A and E, iron, and biotin (also known as Vitamin B7 or Vitamin H, and a part of the B-complex vitamins). Biotin has been scientifically shown to increase fingernail thickness and reduce brittleness and splitting.

name: Kale
properties: Leafy greens contain iron, folate, and calcium. They help make your nails, well, tough as nails.

name: Carrots
properties: Carrots are high in Vitamin A, which provides necessary antioxidants to keep nails protected and strong.

name: Oyster
properties: Zinc is needed for many biological processes, including making proteins like those in your hair and nails.

name: Almonds
properties: Almonds a good source of protein, loaded with magnesium(anti-stress mineral), which helps maintain healthy hair and nails.

name: Blueberries
properties: Antioxidants help protect your body's cells against free radical damage. Blueberries are one of the highest antioxidant properties of all fruits.

name: Salmon
properties: salmon, a fatty fish rich in protein and also in biotin and omega-3 fatty acids, three essential nutrients for lush nails. Salmon is chock full of healthy fats and vitamins B6 and B12, which will keep nails from splitting, breaking, peeling, or otherwise falling apart.
